text.__SUMMARY__: Cyperus nervulosus is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to Australia.The annual sedge typically grows to a height of 0.03 to 0.2 metres (0.10 to 0.66 ft) and has a tufted habit. It blooms between February and July and produces green-brown flowers.In Western Australia it is found around swamps and pools in the Kimberley region where it grows in sandy-clay soils.
